From: Sean V Kelley <sean.v.kelley@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 8 Oct 2020 18:17:33 -0500
Subject: PCI/ERR: Simplify by using pci_upstream_bridge()
Git-repo: git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/pci.git#pci/err
Git-commit: cad59d008a42c461726187ace6bb0f3158c85f7e
Patch-mainline: Queued in subsystem maintainer repository
References: jsc#SLE-13736 jsc#SLE-14845

Use pci_upstream_bridge() in place of dev->bus->self.  No functional change
intended.

[bhelgaas: split to separate patch]
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20201002184735.1229220-6-seanvk.dev@oregontracks.org
Signed-off-by: Sean V Kelley <sean.v.kelley@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Bjorn Helgaas <bhelgaas@google.com>
Acked-by: Jonathan Cameron <Jonathan.Cameron@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/pci/pcie/err.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/pci/pcie/err.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/pcie/err.c
@@ -155,7 +155,7 @@ pci_ers_result_t pcie_do_recovery(struct
 	 */
 	if (!(pci_pcie_type(dev) == PCI_EXP_TYPE_ROOT_PORT ||
 	      pci_pcie_type(dev) == PCI_EXP_TYPE_DOWNSTREAM))
-		dev = dev->bus->self;
+		dev = pci_upstream_bridge(dev);
 	bus = dev->subordinate;
 
 	pci_dbg(dev, "broadcast error_detected message\n");
